text: Simona Bajusz (born Simona Kopecká 28 November 1993) is a Czech volleyball player, playing as a setter. She is part of the Czech Republic women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 2017 Summer Universiade, 2019 Women's European Volleyball League, winning a gold medal. 2022 FIVB Women's Volleyball World Champpionship, and EuroVolley 2023. On club level she played for PVK Olymp Praha, VK Dukla Liberec, and VK Prostějov. == References == Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Czech volleyball players
